n Mussolini's long line of lovers became his intimate and how she came to her violent fate at his side.   R. J. B. Bosworth explores the social climbing of Claretta's family, her naïve and self-interested commitment to fascism, her diary's graphically detailed accounts of sexual life with Mussolini, and much more. Brimful of new and arresting information, the book sheds intimate light not only on an ordinary-extraordinary woman living at the heart of Italy's totalitarian fascist state but also on Mussolini himself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 0aMistresseszItalyvBiography. 0aWomen fascistszItalyvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Women.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300226263423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300226263.jpg  a978-3-11-063898-1  YUP eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles